# Course tracks: `index.html` vs `fce.html` / `ege.html`

The repo ships **multiple entry “courses”**. Treat them as **different products** unless the user explicitly asks to wire the same feature into every track.

## What each file is for

- **`index.html`** — main **CPE Prep** hub (Levels grid, Prep folders, large app shell). This is the primary “Levels hub” home for the CPE workflow.
- **`fce.html`** — **FCE / Mastering B2** course home (player name, unit tiles, progress). Not the same IA as the full CPE hub.
- **`ege.html`** — **EGE** track home (when used).

Netlify **track builds** (`scripts/build-netlify-track.mjs`): on FCE/EGE publish, root `index.html` is replaced with a **stub** that redirects to `fce.html` or `ege.html`, so `/index.html` still resolves but is not the full CPE app on that site.

## Hard rules for agents

1. **Do not** add CPE-only or Prep-specific teaching content (e.g. seeded Level folders, big hub features) to **`fce.html`** unless the user asks for the FCE tile grid to show it.
2. **Do not** link **from** the CPE hub / `index.html` surfaces **to** `fce.html` as “back” or “home” for standard navigation. Users on the CPE flow should return to **`index.html`** (Levels hub), not to the FCE sheet.
3. **Shared unit menus** (`unit1.html` … `unit12.html`) live at repo root and are used by more than one surface. Their **“back / home” link must be `index.html`**, not hardcoded `fce.html`, so CPE users are not dropped into the FCE grid. On **FCE-only deploys**, stub `index.html` forwards to `fce.html` automatically.
4. **`unit10-vocabulary/`** — разные хабы без общих плиток: **`unit10-vocabulary/fce/index.html`** (Mastering B2: phrasals, crimes, titles; домой → **`fce.html`**) и **`unit10-vocabulary/cpe/index.html`** (CPE Prep: books/films/similes; домой → **`index.html`**). Корневой **`unit10-vocabulary/index.html`** только редиректит на `fce/` или `cpe/` по **`?course=`** (без параметра — **`cpe/`**, как прежний дефолт). Упражнения в подпапках используют **`js/u10-vocab-course-context.js`** (**`?course=`** или путь **`…/fce/`** vs **`…/cpe/`**). **`similes/index.html`** — статичная CPE-страница.
5. **`index.html`** auto-redirect to `fce.html` happens only when **`window.__PREP_DEPLOY_TRACK__ === "fce"`** (or profile `courseTrack`), i.e. intentional for that build — do not duplicate that logic in random content pages.

## Wording

Reserve **“FCE”** for the **`fce.html`** / Mastering B2 sheet. Reserve **“Levels hub”** or **“CPE hub”** for **`index.html`**. Avoid copy that implies one is the other.

## `?course=` parameter (Unit 10 vocabulary folder)

Teaching HTML under **`unit10-vocabulary/`** (except **`similes/index.html`**) loads **`js/u10-vocab-course-context.js`**.

- **Mastering B2**: вход с **`unit10.html`** → **`unit10-vocabulary/fce/`**; домой → **`fce.html`**; ссылки несут **`course=fce`** где нужно.
- **CPE Prep**: **`unit10-vocabulary/cpe/`**; домой → **`index.html`**; **`course=cpe`** на упражнениях.

**`similes/index.html`**: статичные ссылки; **no** shared script. Omit **`similes/`** from **publish-fce** (see **`scripts/build-netlify-track.mjs`**).

- **Exercise subpages:** **`u10-back-vocab-index`** → **`…/fce/index.html`** или **`…/cpe/index.html`** с **`course=`**; **`data-u10-levels-depth`** → **`fce.html`** или **`index.html`** per track.

### FCE/EGE publish vs “Levels hub”

On **`publish-fce`** / **`publish-ege`**, root **`index.html`** is a **stub** (see **`scripts/build-netlify-track.mjs`**): a link to **`/index.html`** cannot open the **full CPE Levels hub** — it forwards to **`fce.html`** / **`ege.html`**. Learners who need Prep + Levels hub must use the **`publish-cpe`** (or equivalent) origin; this is a **deploy** boundary, not fixable by relative links alone.

### Prep `back=` on `describing-books-*.html`

When **`course=cpe`**, `?back=` may still override the temporary “Levels hub” left link — sanitize with **`isPrepSafeReturnHref`** (reject `fce.html`, `ege.html`, `unit10.html`). When **`course=fce`**, do **not** apply Prep `back=` overrides (stay on **`fce.html`** home / course-scoped crumbs).
